parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unavailability of parts to repair the Takata airbag recall can lead to a delay in fixing the safety issue, putting drivers and passengers at risk of serious injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: as the issue is related to the unavailability of parts to repair the recall.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the steering wheel to become difficult to maneuver, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The power steering assist fault message is displayed
the steering wheel feels heavy or difficult to turn
the power steering pump becomes loud
the vehicle is unable to be steered
and the AdvanceTrac system is disabled.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering gear can cause the steering wheel to seize or become difficult to turn, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The steering wheel seizes or becomes difficult to turn
the power steering assist fault message is displayed
and the vehicle is unable to be steered.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the EPS system can cause the power steering assist to fail, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The power steering assist fault message is displayed
the steering wheel feels heavy or difficult to turn
and the EPS system fails to provide assistance.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering column can cause the steering wheel to become difficult to turn or seize, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The steering wheel seizes or becomes difficult to turn
and the power steering assist fault message is displayed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS hydraulic control unit can cause the brake pedal to travel to the floor, leading to extended stopping distances, accidents, and potential fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal travels to the floor
the vehicle takes longer to stop
warning lights such as "Check Braking System" and "Service Advancetrac" appear on the instrument panel.
